File: platform/mcp-server/src/extension-protocol.ts, lines 345-346. Current code:
```
const method = parsed.method as string | undefined;
const id = parsed.id as string | number | undefined;
```
Replace with:
```
const method = typeof parsed.method === 'string' ? parsed.method : undefined;
const id = typeof parsed.id === 'string' || typeof parsed.id === 'number' ? parsed.id : undefined;
```
This is inside the handleExtensionMessage function. Check that no downstream code assumes method/id are always defined — they're already typed as `| undefined` so callers already handle the undefined case.

File: platform/cli/src/commands/build.ts, lines 71-78 (convertToolSchemas function). Current code calls z.toJSONSchema() directly. Wrap each call in try-catch. Example:
```
let inputSchema: Record<string, unknown>;
try {
  inputSchema = z.toJSONSchema(tool.input) as Record<string, unknown>;
} catch (err) {
  throw new Error(
    `Tool "${tool.name}" input schema failed to serialize to JSON Schema. ` +
    `Schemas cannot use .transform(), .pipe(), or .preprocess(). ` +
    `${err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err)}`
  );
}
```
Do the same for the output schema call.
